ion>We have shown that the harvesting of one species of carnivore can lead to the extinction of other carnivores and that this effect is transmitted through competition among the prey species. Further experiments have been carried out to test the hypothesis that already impoverished ecosystems are more vulnerable to extinction cascades than intact ecosystems.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>Understanding of how whole systems need to be considered when managing exploited populations (e.g. fish stocks)</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>CA18CD28-824B-4EE8-84EF-CF552A339C20</gtr:id><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Agriculture, Food and Drink,Environment</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/19DF225E-C3AB-4909-BDC4-7D9C195B6424"><gtr:id>19DF225E-C3AB-4909-BDC4-7D9C195B6424</gtr:id><gtr:title>Artificial nighttime light changes aphid-parasitoid population dynamics.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Scientific reports</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/5eba2ce267109c62820a5c9e0b29d646"><gtr:id>5eba2ce267109c62820a5c9e0b29d646</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Sanders D</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2015-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>2045-2322</gtr:issn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/9565E0FC-3CB4-4725-ADC3-19D4BE271FE9"><gtr:id>9565E0FC-3CB4-4725-ADC3-19D4BE271FE9</gtr:id><gtr:title>Experimental Evidence for the Population-Dynamic Mechanisms Underlying Extinction Cascades of Carnivores.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Current biology : CB</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/5eba2ce267109c62820a5